article.headline: Austin Peay 67, Morehead St. 63
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Drake Reed scored 16 points including two free throws with 16 seconds left to lift Austin Peay past Morehead State 67-63 Thursday. Reed's late free throws gave the Governors a 65-61 lead. A layup by Fernandez Lockett wih 17 seconds left made it 63-61. Todd Babington added 11 points for Austin Peay (4-4, 2-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Reserve Kyle Duncan and Lockett had 10 points each. Morehead (2-5, 0-1) was led by Jamyron Steward with 16 points, Leon Buchanan with 13 and Maze Stallworth with 11. Both teams hit 50 percent from the field. Austin Peay led 34-30 at the half. Morehead's last lead was 57-56 with 3:03 left.
